-- England Defender Ledley King Out for Three Weeks With Injury, Sky Reports
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-14T18:09:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/england-defender-ledley-king-out-for-three-weeks-with-injury-sky-reports.html

          
          
             England’s Ledley King is out for
three weeks with a groin tear, Sky Sports reported, citing
sources it didn’t identify.  
 The Tottenham center-back could miss England’s remaining
matches at soccer’s World Cup, which runs until July 11.  
          
          


  


        